  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Test Automation Lead",
  "description": "<ul><li>Develop and implement test strategies that align with ISG QA standards while ensuring compliance with documentation requirements and evidence capture practices</li><li>Define test scope, objectives, success criteria, and quality gates with stakeholders</li><li>Plan and manage the transition roadmap from manual testing to automation, including tool adoption (such as Tosca, Playwright, or equivalent) and potential cloud integration</li><li>Manage and coach the testing team by providing technical leadership, coaching, and performance feedback, while allocating resources effectively across projects.</li><li>Communicate test status, quality metrics, risks, and recommendations clearly.</li><li>Establish best practices and enforce testing methodologies across the team.</li><li>Conduct peer reviews of test artifacts and drive continuous improvement initiatives</li><li>Manage testing activities within secure environments, adhering to security protocols</li><li>Guide structured test design practices to support automation readiness</li><li>Collaborate with the ISG QM Section to align testing activities with organizational quality objectives and provide regular progress and quality outcome reports.</li></ul><p><strong>Essential Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 10 years in software testing or quality assurance with at least 3 years in test management, test lead, or equivalent leadership roles</li><li>Proven experience managing testing teams (5+ members) across multiple concurrent projects</li><li>Strong knowledge of test management methodologies, SDLC, and Agile practices</li><li>Ability to develop test strategies for enterprise systems in secure or regulated environments</li><li>Hands-on experience with automation tools (e.g., Tosca, Selenium, Playwright, or equivalents)</li><li>Proficiency in test management and defect tracking tools (e.g., JIRA)</li><li>Experience working with installation and setup in GSIB/COMET laptops</li></ul><p><strong>Highly Desirable Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or equivalent experience</li><li>Professional testing certifications (e.g., ISTQB Advanced Test Manager, CSTE, or equivalent)</li><li>Certified in Tricentis TOSCA Architect or equivalent advanced automation certification</li><li>Expertise in automation tool implementation and optimization</li><li>Experience with setting up of Tosca in cloud-based environments (e.g. in Government Commercial Cloud) and CI/CD integration</li><li>Experience in government or public sector IT projects</li><li>Knowledge of performance, security, and non-functional testing practices</li></ul>",
